name: The Sea House Fish and Chips

owner.name: The Sea House Fish and Chips (Owner)

address: The Sea House Fish and Chips, 3003 Kingsway #7, Vancouver, BC V5R 4A4

featured_reviews.review_id:
Hubby and I decided to give the Sea House and was pleasantly surprised.  We got the dinner special for two.  The price was good for what we got and the portions were large.  My hubby found it a bit greasy but it's fish and chips. That's what makes it yummy.   I am a big supporter of family business that make afford meals.

We are definitely going back and if you feel like some great greasy food give it a try!

featured_reviews.review_id: This place is amazing. Great prices and tasty fish and chips. The batter is light, crispy and sticks to the fish. Every bite of fish had a bite of crispy batter. The batter didn't fall off the fish like many places. Not to mention the fish was super moist. Chips were good and slaw was nice and tangy. What a nice meal to end the week !

featured_reviews.review_id: Hidden gem for fish and chips. Great deal on high quality halibut. The fish is fresh, thick, moist inside with a crispy layer outside. House cut fries and homemade tartar sauce were amazing! Best part, they value providing high quality food such as using Canadian made vegetable oil as opposed to canola oil, which greatly impacted the flavour and didn't make the texture overly greasy. Friendly, respectful and kind service at this family run restaurant.

featured_reviews.review_id: A great unassuming fish and chips place that my husband and I happened to come across. The interior is pretty basic and nothing to write home about, but the food was delicious and service quick. I got the halibut which was fried to perfection - crisp on the outside, juicy on the inside. The fries and coleslaw were also fantastic though I would've liked a bit more slaw because it was so good. Husband got the regular fish (we're assuming cod) which was also delicious and cheaper than halibut. He got the chowder with his combo which lacked salt but was an easy fix and would be good for those trying to be mindful of their salt intake. We were the only customers for a while on a Tuesday at lunch so you wouldn't have to wait long if you're in a rush. We will definitely be back!

featured_reviews.review_id: I was super impressed by this place and almost cried for the quality and price. How can this be so cheap but tasty?? The combo is less than $7 and it includes fish, chips, seafood chowder soup, coleslaw, mayo sauce, ketchup. And one of the staff approached to me and asked how the food is. I can see that they are so caring of customers. Everything was great, but the greatest one was seafood soup. I was really craving for a cream soup, and I was fully satisfied with this soup. The French fries were ordinary though. The black coffee was instant one but it was only $1.5, so I liked it. I will visit again for sure !!!

featured_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Hello Vero Vero, thank you so much for your honest and heartfelt review. We are very humbled. We have been frying fish and chips the old way for almost three decades. Same price, same quality and same heart. Thank you and please come back soon. We are getting old and don't know how long we will last. One dish and one day at a time we go.

featured_reviews.review_id: This place is not at all fancy, but it has the best fish and chips I've found in Vancouver. The crust was beautiful and crispy, while the fish was perfectly cooked on the inside. Not at all over-cooked and dry. It was perfect.

featured_reviews.response_from_owner_text: You are the best. Thank you, sir!!!!!

featured_reviews.review_id: Stunned by the hospitality of the aged owner from Hong Kong, reminds me of those family-own chippy in London, UK (always forget there's London in Canada). The hand cut chips are sooo great and sadly no fresh halibut until summer. Batter is thin and just right. And they have malt vinegar! If there's HP sauce I would be more than delighted. Will definitely come back and chat with them.
